"n.滑轮；滑车 【英】 n.滑轮，滑车(a wheel used to transmit power by means of a band, belt, cord, rope, or chain passing over its rim[轮缘]) 【记】 pull(拉)＋ey n. 滑轮(用一个拉绳穿过的有槽的轮子, 通过改变拉力的方向而拉起重物) 【记】读: 不累－用滑轮组可以省力 【记】pull 拉 + 音：力，物理学中拉力常用滑轮表示 pulley (n.)  late 13c., from Old French polie, pulie ""pulley, windlass"" (12c.) and directly from Medieval Latin poliva, puliva, probably from Medieval Greek *polidia, plural of *polidion ""little pivot,"" diminutive of Greek polos ""pivot, axis"" (see pole (n.2)). As a verb from 1590s."
